<subSubSection lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="47" pageId="6" pageNumber="45" type="key">
<keyStep pageId="6" pageNumber="45">
<paragraph blockId="6.[317,1270,510,536]" box="[317,1270,510,536]" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">
<keyLead box="[317,1270,510,536]" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">1 Stout, spine-like setae on dorsum present 2</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[317,1269,563,589]" box="[317,1269,563,589]" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">
<keyLead box="[317,1269,563,589]" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">– Stout, spine-like setae on dorsum absent 13</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="6" pageNumber="45">
<paragraph blockId="6.[317,1270,615,677]" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">
<keyLead pageId="6" pageNumber="45">
2 Stout, spine-like setae (
<figureCitation box="[653,736,615,641]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[317,352,1759,1780]" captionTargetBox="[385,1203,429,1723]" captionTargetId="figure-17@2.[378,1208,424,1731]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 1. Adult female of G. baloghi KIANEK et KONCZNÉ BENEDICTY sp. n., with an addition of a stout, blunted seta on the head of G. coffeae (a), and a blunted seta on anal lobes of the G.radicum (b)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5731854" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5731854/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">Fig. 1a</figureCitation>
) present on head and on posterior abdominal segment of dorsum 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Green" authorityYear="1933" box="[1149,1270,651,677]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Geococcus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="6" pageNumber="45" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="coffeae">
<emphasis box="[1149,1270,651,677]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">G. coffeae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[317,1270,703,765]" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">
<keyLead pageId="6" pageNumber="45">
– Stout, spine-like setae present only on posterior abdominal segment of dorsum (
<figureCitation box="[442,510,739,765]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[317,352,1759,1780]" captionTargetBox="[385,1203,429,1723]" captionTargetId="figure-17@2.[378,1208,424,1731]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 1. Adult female of G. baloghi KIANEK et KONCZNÉ BENEDICTY sp. n., with an addition of a stout, blunted seta on the head of G. coffeae (a), and a blunted seta on anal lobes of the G.radicum (b)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5731854" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5731854/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
) 3
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="6" pageNumber="45">
<paragraph blockId="6.[317,1270,791,817]" box="[317,1270,791,817]" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">
<keyLead box="[317,1270,791,817]" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">
3 Stout, spine-like setae blunt (
<figureCitation box="[720,802,791,817]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[317,352,1759,1780]" captionTargetBox="[385,1203,429,1723]" captionTargetId="figure-17@2.[378,1208,424,1731]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 1. Adult female of G. baloghi KIANEK et KONCZNÉ BENEDICTY sp. n., with an addition of a stout, blunted seta on the head of G. coffeae (a), and a blunted seta on anal lobes of the G.radicum (b)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5731854" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5731854/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">Fig. 1c</figureCitation>
) 4
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[317,1270,844,870]" box="[317,1270,844,870]" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">
<keyLead box="[317,1270,844,870]" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">
– Stout, spine-like setae not blunt (
<figureCitation box="[764,832,844,870]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[317,352,1759,1780]" captionTargetBox="[385,1203,429,1723]" captionTargetId="figure-17@2.[378,1208,424,1731]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 1. Adult female of G. baloghi KIANEK et KONCZNÉ BENEDICTY sp. n., with an addition of a stout, blunted seta on the head of G. coffeae (a), and a blunted seta on anal lobes of the G.radicum (b)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5731854" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5731854/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
) 5
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="6" pageNumber="45">
<paragraph blockId="6.[317,1270,897,923]" box="[317,1270,897,923]" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">
<keyLead box="[317,1270,897,923]" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">
4 Stout, spine-like setae short, as long as wide 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Green" authorityYear="1902" box="[1136,1270,897,923]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Geococcus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="6" pageNumber="45" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="radicum">
<emphasis box="[1136,1270,897,923]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">G. radicum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[317,1270,950,976]" box="[317,1270,950,976]" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">
<keyLead box="[317,1270,950,976]" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">
– Stout, spine-like setae three times longer than wide 
<emphasis box="[1126,1270,950,976]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">G. eliquatus</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="6" pageNumber="45">
<paragraph blockId="6.[317,1269,1003,1029]" box="[317,1269,1003,1029]" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">
<keyLead box="[317,1269,1003,1029]" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">
5 Stout, spine-like setae situated on the outher margin of anal lobes 
<emphasis box="[1146,1269,1003,1029]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">G. hauseri</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[317,1270,1055,1081]" box="[317,1270,1055,1081]" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">
<keyLead box="[317,1270,1055,1081]" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">– Stout, spine-like setae situated on the inner margin of anal lobes 6</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="6" pageNumber="45">
<paragraph blockId="6.[317,1269,1108,1134]" box="[317,1269,1108,1134]" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">
<keyLead box="[317,1269,1108,1134]" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">
6 With two stout, spine-like setae on inner margin of anal lobes 
<emphasis box="[1164,1269,1108,1134]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">G. latens</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[317,1270,1161,1187]" box="[317,1270,1161,1187]" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">
<keyLead box="[317,1270,1161,1187]" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">– With one stout, spine-like setae on inner margin of anal lobes 7</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="6" pageNumber="45">
<paragraph blockId="6.[317,1270,1214,1240]" box="[317,1270,1214,1240]" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">
<keyLead box="[317,1270,1214,1240]" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">7 Stout, spine-like setae weakly developed, almost hair-like 8</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[317,1270,1267,1293]" box="[317,1270,1267,1293]" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">
<keyLead box="[317,1270,1267,1293]" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">– Stout, spine-like setae strongly developed 9</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="6" pageNumber="45">
<paragraph blockId="6.[317,1270,1319,1381]" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">
<keyLead pageId="6" pageNumber="45">
8 Some hair-like setae with a minute seta at the base, all multilocular pores with six loculi 
<emphasis box="[1118,1270,1355,1381]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">G. satellitum</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[317,1270,1407,1469]" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">
<keyLead pageId="6" pageNumber="45">
– Hair-like setae without minute seta at the base, multilocular pores mostly with four loculi 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Williams" authorityYear="1969" box="[1118,1270,1443,1469]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Geococcus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="6" pageNumber="45" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lawrencei">
<emphasis box="[1118,1270,1443,1469]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">G. lawrencei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="6" pageNumber="45">
<paragraph blockId="6.[317,1270,1495,1522]" box="[317,1270,1495,1522]" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">
<keyLead box="[317,1270,1495,1522]" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">
9 Dorsum of head with several robust, hair-like setae (
<figureCitation box="[993,1077,1495,1521]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[317,352,1759,1780]" captionTargetBox="[385,1203,429,1723]" captionTargetId="figure-17@2.[378,1208,424,1731]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 1. Adult female of G. baloghi KIANEK et KONCZNÉ BENEDICTY sp. n., with an addition of a stout, blunted seta on the head of G. coffeae (a), and a blunted seta on anal lobes of the G.radicum (b)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5731854" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5731854/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">Fig. 1b</figureCitation>
) 
<taxonomicName authorityName="KIANEK et KONCZNE BENEDICTY" authorityYear="2007" box="[1144,1270,1496,1522]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Geococcus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="6" pageNumber="45" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="baloghi">
<emphasis box="[1144,1270,1496,1522]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">G. baloghi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[317,1269,1548,1574]" box="[317,1269,1548,1574]" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">
<keyLead box="[317,1269,1548,1574]" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">– Dorsum of head without robust, hair-like setae 10</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="6" pageNumber="45">
<paragraph blockId="6.[317,1269,1601,1627]" box="[317,1269,1601,1627]" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">
<keyLead box="[317,1269,1601,1627]" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">10 Lateral dorsal margin of abdominal segment VII sclerotized 11</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[317,1269,1654,1680]" box="[317,1269,1654,1680]" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">
<keyLead box="[317,1269,1654,1680]" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">– Lateral dorsal margin of abdominal segment VII not sclerotized 12</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<paragraph blockId="6.[317,1269,1707,1768]" lastBlockId="7.[317,1269,439,501]" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="46" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">
<keyLead lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="46" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">
<keyStep lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="46" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">
11 Only a weakly developed circulus present. Tritubular pores on middorsum of venter absent 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lit" authorityYear="1992" box="[1111,1269,1742,1768]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Geococcus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="6" pageNumber="45" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="associatus">
<emphasis box="[1111,1269,1742,1768]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">G. associatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
– With two, well developed circuli. Tritubular pores on middorsum present 
<emphasis box="[1103,1269,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="46">G. johoriensis</emphasis>
</keyStep>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[317,1270,527,554]" box="[317,1270,527,554]" pageId="7" pageNumber="46">
<keyLead box="[317,1270,527,554]" pageId="7" pageNumber="46">
<keyStep box="[317,1270,527,554]" pageId="7" pageNumber="46">
12 Ostioles not surrounded with multilocular pores 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kuwana" authorityYear="1923" box="[1144,1270,528,554]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Geococcus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="7" pageNumber="46" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="citrinus">
<emphasis box="[1144,1270,528,554]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="46">G. citrinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyStep>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[317,1270,580,606]" lastBlockId="8.[317,1269,439,466]" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="47" pageId="7" pageNumber="46">
<keyLead box="[317,1270,580,606]" pageId="7" pageNumber="46">
– Ostioles surrounded with multilocular pores 
<emphasis box="[1131,1270,580,606]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="46">G. detonsus</emphasis>
</keyLead>
<keyLead box="[317,1269,439,466]" pageId="8" pageNumber="47">
<keyStep box="[317,1269,439,466]" pageId="8" pageNumber="47">
13 Multilocular pores on dorsum absent 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Kuwana" baseAuthorityYear="1907" box="[1155,1269,440,466]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Geococcus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="8" pageNumber="47" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="oryzae">
<emphasis box="[1155,1269,440,466]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="47">G. oryzae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyStep>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
